![](Take-home_Ex03_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-10-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: :::callout-tip According to the VAST2024 - MC3 Data Description, the person node include Entity.Person and Entity.Person.CEO, the other were included in the Company. ::: ## 3 MC3 Task(3) Develop a visual approach to examine inferences. Infer how the influence of a company changes through time. Can you infer ownership and influence that a network may have? ::: callout-tip Based on this plot, the edge types like {Shareholdership, BeneficialOwnership, WorksFor, FamilyRelationship} will be used, and the company name to define company; Meanwhile, the type in node like (Entity.Organization, Entity.Organization.Company, Entity.Organization.FishingCompany, Entity.Organization.LogisticsCompany, Entity.Organization.NewsCompany, Entity.Organization.FinancialCompany, Entity.Organization.NGO) will be used, source and target will be choosed to decide the "from" and "to". ::: ### 3.1 Relationship #### 3.1.1 Nodes The code chunk below will be used to extract the nodes data.frame of mc3_data and save it as a tibble data.frame called mc3_nodes. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} mc3_nodes_clean <- as_tibble(mc3_data$nodes) %>% mutate(type = as.character(type), id = as.character(id)) %>% select(id, type) kable(head(mc3_nodes_clean)) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} |id |type | |:---------------------------|:---------------------------| |Abbott, Mcbride and Edwards |Entity.Organization.Company | |Abbott-Gomez |Entity.Organization.Company | |Abbott-Harrison |Entity.Organization.Company | |Abbott-Ibarra |Entity.Organization.Company | |Abbott-Sullivan |Entity.Organization.Company | |Acevedo and Sons |Entity.Organization.Company | ::: ::: #### 3.1.2 Edges The code chunk below will be used to extract the links data.frame of mc3_data and save it as a tibble data.frame called mc3_edges. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} mc3_edges_clean <- as_tibble(mc3_data$links) %>% distinct() %>% mutate(source = as.character(source), target = as.character(target), type = as.character(type)) %>% group_by(source, target, type) %>% summarise(weights = n()) %>% filter(source!=target) %>% ungroup() kable(head(mc3_edges_clean)) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} |source |target |type | weights| |:----------------------|:------------------------------------|:------------------------------|-------:| |4. SeaCargo Ges.m.b.H. |Dry CreekRybachit Marine A/S |Event.Owns.Shareholdership | 1| |4. SeaCargo Ges.m.b.H. |KambalaSea Freight Inc |Event.Owns.Shareholdership | 1| |9. RiverLine CJSC |SumacAmerica Transport GmbH & Co. KG |Event.Owns.Shareholdership | 1| |Aaron Acosta |Manning-Pratt |Event.Owns.Shareholdership | 1| |Aaron Acosta |Manning-Pratt |Event.WorksFor | 1| |Aaron Allen |Hicks-Calderon |Event.Owns.BeneficialOwnership | 1| ::: ::: ### 3.2 Visualising network graph First, create a graph object using tbl_graph() function. Then calculate betweenness and closeness centrality scores. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} mc3_graph <- tbl_graph(nodes = mc3_nodes_clean, edges = mc3_edges_clean, directed = FALSE) %>% mutate(betweenness_centrality = centrality_betweenness(), closeness_centrality = centrality_closeness()) ``` ::: We will filter nodes with high betweenness centrality scores (>8,000,000) and visualise them to see the relationships that they have. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} set.seed(1234) mc3_graph %>% filter(betweenness_centrality >= 8000000) %>% ggraph(layout = "fr") + geom_edge_link(aes(#width= weights, alpha=0.5)) + geom_node_point(aes( size = betweenness_centrality, color = type, alpha = 0.3)) + geom_node_label(aes(label = id),repel=TRUE, size=2.5, alpha = 0.8) + scale_size_continuous(range=c(1,10)) + theme_graph() + labs(title = 'Initial network visualisation', subtitle = 'Entities with betweenness scores > 8,000,000') ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](Take-home_Ex03_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-14-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: Below is a dataframe showing us the top 10 entities with the highest betweenness scores. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} mc3_graph %>% activate(nodes) %>% as_tibble() %>% arrange(desc(betweenness_centrality)) %>% slice(1:10) %>% kable() ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} |id |type | betweenness_centrality| closeness_centrality| |:---------------------------|:------------------------------------|----------------------:|--------------------:| |Sharon Moon |Entity.Person | 30681485| 3.5e-06| |Steven Robertson |Entity.Person | 29237593| 3.1e-06| |Hart Ltd |Entity.Organization.FinancialCompany | 27532594| 3.1e-06| |Johnson, Morales and Castro |Entity.Organization.Company | 26615081| 3.5e-06| |Abbott-Harrison |Entity.Organization.Company | 24715901| 2.9e-06| |Morrison-Zamora |Entity.Organization.Company | 22116507| 3.5e-06| |Phelps, Montoya and Barnett |Entity.Organization.Company | 21052612| 2.9e-06| |Holloway-Salas |Entity.Organization.Company | 20760807| 3.6e-06| |Michael Howard DDS |Entity.Person | 20285433| 3.4e-06| |Mills, Atkinson and Chavez |Entity.Organization.Company | 20119719| 3.0e-06| ::: ::: The top 10 betweenness entities above are not dealing with relationship between fish companies. In the next section, we will filter entities into only organization entities. We may revisit the person entities later when we have specific targets/companies to investigate. ### 3.3 Exploring the VisNetwork #### 3.3.1 Extract edges related to organization nodes ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} mc3_nodes_select <- mc3_nodes_clean %>% filter(grepl("Entity\\.Organization", type, ignore.case = TRUE)) mc3_edges_select <- mc3_edges_clean %>% filter(source %in% mc3_nodes_select$id | target %in% mc3_nodes_select$id) %>% distinct() %>% rename(from = source, to = target) # Extract edges with more than or equal to 8 links mc3_edges_select_high <- mc3_edges_select %>% group_by(from) %>% mutate(count = n()) %>% filter(count >= 40) %>% ungroup() ``` ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} # Get distinct Source and Target nodes mc3_nodes_source <- mc3_edges_select_high %>% distinct(from) %>% rename(id = from) mc3_nodes_target <- mc3_edges_select_high %>% distinct(to) %>% rename(id = to) ``` ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} mc3_nodes_combined <- bind_rows(mc3_nodes_source, mc3_nodes_target) # Assign group based on type mc3_nodes_combined$group <- ifelse(mc3_nodes_combined$id %in% mc3_nodes_select$id, "Entity Organization", "Entity.Person") # Visualize with visNetwork visNetwork(mc3_nodes_combined, mc3_edges_select) %>% visPhysics(solver = "forceAtlas2Based", forceAtlas2Based = list(gravitationalConstant = -100)) %>% visIgraphLayout(layout = "layout_with_fr") %>% visGroups(groupname = "Entity Organization", color = "yellow") %>% visGroups(groupname = "Entity Person", color = "grey") %>% visLegend() %>% visEdges(arrows = "to") %>% visOptions( highlightNearest = list(enabled = TRUE, degree = 2, hover = TRUE), nodesIdSelection = TRUE, selectedBy = "group", collapse = TRUE ) %>% visInteraction(dragNodes = TRUE, dragView = TRUE, zoomView = TRUE) %>% visEvents(selectNode = "function(properties) { var selectedNodeId = properties.nodes[0]; this.body.data.nodes.update({id: selectedNodeId, color: {background: 'red', border: 'black'}}); }") ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ```{=html}
